EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 182300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED OVER THE BALTIC SEA 1046
AND WILL EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS THE NERN BRITISH ISLES. THIS HIGH WILL REMAIN
IN SITU FOR MUCH OF THE PERIOD BUT DECLINE TO 1037 BY TUESDAY. IN THE MEANTIME
THE RIDGE OVER THE UK WILL GRADUALLY BE DISPLACED BY A SHALLOW LOW 1026
TRAVELLING N ALONG THE E COAST OF ENGLAND CENTRED VIKING MONDAY EVENING
AND LOSING ITS IDENTITY THEREAFTER. THROUGH TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY THE HIGH
OVER THE BALTIC SEA WILL GRADUALLY BECOME DISPLACED OVER THE BRITISH ISLES.
THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD LOW PRESSURE SYSTEMS WILL DEVELOP IN THE MID-ATLANTIC
SOME MAKING PROGRESS N AND E AS THEY APPROACH ICELAND WHILST OTHERS BECOME
DEFLECTED TOWARD IBERIA AND HEAD TOWARD THE STRAIT OF GIBRALTAR. STRG WINDS
LIKELY INITIALLY IN EERN AND NERN CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS THESE BECMG INCRLY
